statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

articles.headline: Benigni's 24 help Navy upset Bucknell 83-77 in Patriot League Tournament semifinals
articles.description: — Austin Benigni had 24 points in fifth-seeded Navy's 83-77 upset over top-seeded Bucknell on Sunday in the Patriot League Tournament.

articles.headline: Williamson scores 32 as Towson defeats Drexel 82-76 in Coastal Athletic Association Tournament
articles.description: — Dylan Williamson's 32 points led top-seeded Towson over eighth-seeded Drexel 82-76 on Sunday in the in the quarterfinals of the Coastal Athletic Association Tournament.

articles.headline: Bubble Watch 2025: Conference locks for men's March Madness
articles.description: As Selection Sunday nears, let's track which teams can play their way in or out of the NCAA tournament.

images.name: Porter Moser [1296x729]
images.caption: Porter Moser's Oklahoma squad played itself into a new category of ESPN's Bubble Watch with Saturday's win over Texas.

images.name: Billy Richmond III's clutch block seals dramatic win for Arkansas
images.caption: Riley Kugel's last-second shot is denied by Billy Richmond III as Arkansas hangs on to beat Mississippi State.

articles.headline: No. 8 Michigan State tops No. 17 Michigan 79-62, winning the 18-school Big Ten title by 3 games
articles.description: — Tre Holloman scored a career-high 20 points, Jase Richardson had 18 points and No. 8 Michigan State beat No. 17 Michigan 79-62 on Sunday.

images.name: Tre Holloman initiates scuffle with Michigan players standing on logo
images.caption: Michigan State's Tre Holloman takes offense to Michigan players standing on the Spartan logo during senior day ceremonies.

articles.headline: Florida State hires Luke Loucks to 5-year deal as basketball coach
articles.description: Luke Loucks will succeed Leonard Hamilton as Florida State men's basketball coach, signing a five-year deal. "It's like it was meant to be," Loucks said.

images.name: Leonard Hamilton's final game as FSU coach is his 200th ACC win
images.caption: Leonard Hamilton finishes his coaching career at Florida State with a win over SMU, his 200th victory in ACC play.
